<div align='center'><font size='4'><b>A MILLSBUCK SAVED IS A MILLSBUCK EARNED</b></font><br>
<img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/gazette_20071129.jpg' border='1'>
</div>
<br>
<b>Thursday, November 29, 2007</b> &mdash; Saving money is often a challenging thing for anyone to do. Why save what you can spend? Why save at all?<br><br>There are three main reasons to save money. The first is that life is often unpredictable.  You never know what will happen tomorrow, and it&#039;s always best to be financially prepared for the unknown.<br>
<br>
The second is that you may have something in mind that you can&#039;t afford now and will have to save money for. This could be anything from new clothes, to college, to new home improvements.  With the holidays quickly approaching, you&#039;ll probably want to start saving to buy presents for friends and family.<br><br>The third reason may have never occurred to you before. By saving money, you can actually make your money work for you. That&#039;s right, you&#039;re money can actually work for you to make you more money.  <br><br>The best place to put your Millsbucks to work is at the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/bank/">Millsberry Mercantile Bank</a>. They&#039;re not going to be working as a Teller or the Bank Manager, but in a savings account. In your savings account, your Millsbucks can earn you interest. <br><br>Interest is money paid at a regular rate, which is usually a percentage, for money being lent. This may sound like Greek to you, but it&#039;s actually simpler than it appears. When you put your money in a savings account, what you&#039;re actually doing is lending your money to the bank temporarily.  In return for lending your money to the bank, they repay you with interest, which is how you make more money. <br><br>You accumulate interest gradually, so you&#039;ll have to leave your money in your savings account untouched for a while to make any real positive change to your account balance. It&#039;s a game of patience, but on the positive side, there&#039;s no risk involved. <br><br>You can even use your interest rate to calculate what your money will be worth in the future. This is called the Future Value, and it&#039;s really helpful when you&#039;re making goals for how much money you need to save. Setting goals for savings is a very important part of the process and should be one of the first things you do. <br><br>Saving money is one of the easiest ways to make your dreams a reality. All you really need is time, some Millsbucks, and a savings account. Then you can sit back and relax as your money puts in the long hours for you.<br></div>
